reviews.review_text:
Sounds like the other Oade source Enough has been said about the show, I've been listening to this to determine if there is any difference in sound quality from the other Oade aud offered here, and I can't discern a difference.
It's a typically good audience recording by the Oade bros. Captures the essential sound of the pavillion for those who enjoy these things. Not too much chatter, although one guy within earshot has a contagious laugh.
A very nice recording of a very nice show which I have absolutely no recollection of - The night before I recall very well! Lots of brain cells under the bridge...
LP
20 years ago tonite........... summer 85 was a great time for a tour and  a great time for recordings as well. enjoy this show.  aloha and mahalo!

Stellar show - Red gels I remember kickin around in the lot before the show just about to peak on some half doz. really clean red gels while we were crossing the walk-over bridge to get into the show. Stellar show / setlist also the sound that night was great and I remember during scarlet-fire I saw a bunch of heads raising, above the ground, another long haired beirded head as he lay flat and still, at the top of the field part of the pavillion. It was way trippy and my first outside dead show 
very very kool......
Solid Show Love the FOTM, Jerry adds some nice licks at the end. Great show all the way around.

Smokin' Crater... I love this show.  I think the night before gets more attention, not that it's not awesome, but I prefer this one of the two.  The Scarlet-Fire is rippin', esp. the end of Fire - out of control.  Post-Drums is as 'rock and roll' as it gets, can't get enough. :)
Walkin Blues Best one ever. Hot show
Grate Show! And I do prefer this warm Oaude aud over the soundboards!  Feels like I’m right there!
